HEADWORD: Occecation
<hw>Oc*ce*ca"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>occaecatio</ets>, fr. <ets>occaecare</ets> to make blind; <ets>ob +
caecare</ets> to blind, fr. <ets>caecus</ets> blind.]</ety> <def>The act
of making blind, or the state of being blind.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>
⟦ldquo⟧This inward <xex>occecation</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Bp.
